Packaging
Labeling
- FCC: USA, electronics radiation limits
- TÜV: Germany, technical certification
- CE: EU, health and safety standards
- registered trademark ®: symbol or word representing brand
- trademark ™: unregistered
Logistics
Retailing
Recycling

#Hazardous materials (HAZMAT)
explosives (dynamite)
flammable (hydrogen)
poisonous (chlorine)
infectious (virus)
radioactive (uranium)
corrosive (acid)

#Energy consumption - production
Glass
- energy 1kg: 2kWh (recycled 1kWh)
Paper
- energy 1kg: 3kWh
Steel
- energy 1kg: 5kWh (recycled 3kWh)
Plastics
- energy 1kg: 20kWh (recycled 10-15kWh)
Aluminium
- energy 1kg: 50kWh (recycled 5kWh)

#Refinery: large chemical plant
transforms petroleum (crude oil) into gasoline, diesel, asphalt and other products
global: 100M barrels/day
countries
- USA (20M)
- China
- Russia
- India
- South Korea
- Japan
largest
- Jamnagar, Gujarat
- Paraguana, Venezuela
- Ulsan, South Korea
- Ruwais, UAE
- Yeosu, South Korea

#Petrol
sweet: low sulphur content (0.5%), more valuable
sour: high sulphur content (2%)
Benchmark: reference price
- West Texas Intermediate (WTI): sweet, USA
- Brent: sweet, Europe
- Dubai: sour, Middle East
- Urals: sour, Russia

#Battery
Sizes:
- AA: 1.5V, ~2000 mAh, electronics
- AAA: 1.5V, ~1000 mAh, electronics
- AAAA: laser pointers
- C
- D
- PP3: 9V, smoke alarms
- CRXXYY: 3V, lithium manganese oxide, coin shape, size XX/YY mm
- CR2016: watches
- CR2025
- CR2032: most common CR
- CR2450
- SRXX: silver oxide, coin shape
- LRXX: alkaline, coin shape
